# Harbor integration: header-propagation and request-shape battery.
#
# Catches the regression class where a proxy mangles the request before it
# reaches the model server: dropping observability headers (X-Request-Id),
# rewriting Content-Type, gzipping a body the upstream did not opt into,
# or smuggling extra fields. /v1/debug/echo on the mock returns the
# request verbatim so we can assert end-to-end that the body and headers
# the user sent are the body and headers the upstream observed.
#
# The latency knob (?latency_ms=N) is a wall-clock check that the mock is
# reachable through whatever runtime is in front of it (compose net, podman
# rootless slirp4netns, etc.) without artificial buffering.

@mock_openai_port = 29350
@base_url = http://localhost:{{mock_openai_port}}

### X-Request-Id is round-tripped on /health
# @name request-id-roundtrip
GET {{base_url}}/health
X-Request-Id: harbor-rid-aaaa-bbbb-cccc

?? status == 200
?? header X-Request-Id == harbor-rid-aaaa-bbbb-cccc

###

### Latency knob delays response by ?latency_ms
# @name latency-knob
GET {{base_url}}/health?latency_ms=250

?? status == 200
?? duration > 200
?? duration < 5000

###

### Echo endpoint round-trips JSON body verbatim
# @name echo-json-body
POST {{base_url}}/v1/debug/echo
Content-Type: application/json
X-Custom-Field: harbor-test-value

{
  "alpha": 1,
  "beta": "two",
  "nested": {"gamma": [3, 4, 5]}
}

?? status == 200
?? body method == POST
?? body path == /v1/debug/echo
?? body json_body.alpha == 1
?? body json_body.beta == two
?? js response.parsedBody.json_body.nested.gamma[2] == 5
# httpyac (Node http) sends header names lowercased; the echo reflects the
# wire form rather than the canonical case. Asserting on the wire form
# catches the case where a proxy upper-cases or rewrites header names.
?? js response.parsedBody.headers["x-custom-field"] == harbor-test-value

###

### Echo endpoint preserves Content-Type
# @name echo-content-type
POST {{base_url}}/v1/debug/echo
Content-Type: application/json

{"probe": "ok"}

?? status == 200
?? js response.parsedBody.headers["content-type"] == application/json

###
